# DLP egress allowlist -- consumed by .claude/hooks/check_egress_allowlist.py
#
# This .example file is INERT. To switch the egress hook from warn-only to
# BLOCK mode, copy it to `egress_allowlist.txt` (same dir) and edit:
#
#     cp .claude/dlp/egress_allowlist.txt.example .claude/dlp/egress_allowlist.txt
#
# Once egress_allowlist.txt exists, any data-upload command (curl/wget upload,
# scp/rsync/sftp, nc) to a host NOT listed here is BLOCKED (exit 2).
#
# Format: one host or dot-suffix per line. `#` starts a comment.
#   api.example.com        -> matches exactly that host
#   .internal.example.com  -> matches any subdomain (foo.internal.example.com)
# Built-in always-allowed (no need to list): localhost 127.0.0.1 ::1 0.0.0.0
#
# An EMPTY egress_allowlist.txt = block ALL exfil to non-local hosts (max lockdown).

# --- add your legitimate egress destinations below ---
# api.openai.com
# api.anthropic.com
# hooks.slack.com
# .s3.amazonaws.com
# uploads.mycompany.com
